Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Idioti* su izgubili kontrolu nad svojim ponašanjem. (The idiots lost control of their behavior.)
2. Ne mogu verovati koliko *idioti* imaju uticaja na društvo. (I can't believe how much influence idiots have on society.)
3. On je jedan od najvećih *idiotima* koje sam ikada upoznao. (He is one of the biggest idiots I have ever met.)
4. Izvinite što sam rekao da ste *idioti*, nisam to mislio ozbiljno. (I'm sorry for calling you idiots, I didn't mean it seriously.)
5. Svi smo mislili da je ideja bila dobra, ali sada se ispostavilo da smo *idioti*. (We all thought the idea was good, but now it turns out we were idiots.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "idioti" is the plural form of "idiot", which means the same thing in English.